entry.tran: （与数字连用构成名词）表示“重…磅的动物（或鱼）”
entry.def: -pounder can be added to numbers to form nouns that refer to animals or fish that weigh a particular number of pounds.

example.ex: My fish average 2 lb 8 oz and I've had two eight-pounders.
example.tran: 我的鱼平均每条重2磅8盎司，还有过两条重8磅的。

entry.tran: （与数字连用构成名词）表示“发射…磅重炮弹的大炮”
entry.def: -pounder can be added to numbers to  form nouns that refer to guns that fire shells weighing a particular number of pounds.

example.tran: 这些大炮发射12磅重的炮弹。

means.word_mean: 1. (used only in combination) something weighing a given number of pounds;
2. a heavy tool of stone or iron (usually with a flat base and a handle) that is used to grind and mix material (as grain or drugs or pigments) against a slab of stone
